# DataTable Filter Pattern — Mandatory Rules

> **⛔ NEVER use `FilterModal` from Circuit DS or build inline filter forms. ALWAYS use a `Dialog` with `FormField`-wrapped inputs.**

Every DataTable that needs filtering MUST follow this exact pattern. No exceptions.

## 1. Architecture — Draft / Applied State

Filters use a **two-layer state** model managed by a composable:

- **Applied** refs — drive actual data filtering and chip display
- **Draft** refs — edited inside the Dialog; only committed on "Apply"

```ts
// Applied state (drives filtering)
const appliedUsers = ref<string[]>([]);
const appliedStatus = ref<string>('All');

// Draft state (edited in dialog)
const draftUsers = ref<string[]>([]);
const draftStatus = ref<string>('All');
```

**Open dialog** → copy applied → draft. **Apply** → copy draft → applied, close. **Cancel** → just close.

```ts
function openFilterDialog() {
  draftUsers.value = [...appliedUsers.value];
  draftStatus.value = appliedStatus.value;
  showFilterDialog.value = true;
}

function applyFilters() {
  appliedUsers.value = [...draftUsers.value];
  appliedStatus.value = draftStatus.value;
  showFilterDialog.value = false;
}

function cancelFilterDialog() {
  showFilterDialog.value = false;
}
```

## 2. Filter Dialog — Always Use `Dialog` + `FormField`

The filter dialog is a standard Circuit DS `Dialog` containing `FormField`-wrapped inputs.

### Supported Input Types Inside FormField

| Input Type | Component | Use When |
|---|---|---|
| Multi-select dropdown | `MultiSelect` from `primevue/multiselect` | Multiple values from a list (users, servers, tags) |
| Single-select dropdown | `Select` from `primevue/select` | One value from a list |
| Segmented toggle | `SelectButton` from `primevue/selectbutton` | Small set of mutually exclusive options (All/Active/Inactive) |
| Text search | `InputText` from `primevue/inputtext` | Free-text filter |

### Dialog Template

```html
<Dialog
  :visible="showFilterDialog"
  :draggable="false"
  modal
  header="Apply filters"
  :style="{ width: '560px' }"
  @update:visible="!$event && emit('cancelFilterDialog')"
>
  <template #closeicon><XMarkIcon /></template>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-md">
    <FormField label="User">
      <template #default="{ inputId }">
        <MultiSelect
          :id="inputId"
          :modelValue="draftUsers"
          :options="userOptions"
          optionLabel="label"
          optionValue="value"
          placeholder="All users"
          :maxSelectedLabels="2"
          class="w-full"
          @update:modelValue="emit('update:draftUsers', $event)"
        />
      </template>
    </FormField>

    <FormField label="Status">
      <template #default="{ inputId }">
        <SelectButton
          :id="inputId"
          :modelValue="draftStatus"
          :options="statusOptions"
          :allowEmpty="false"
          @update:modelValue="emit('update:draftStatus', $event)"
        />
      </template>
    </FormField>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer: left info + right buttons — MUST NOT wrap -->
  <template #footer>
    <div class="flex items-center flex-1 min-w-0">
      <span class="text-body-sm text-neutral-subtle">{{ draftFilterCount }} Filters applied</span>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-sm shrink-0">
      <Button label="Cancel" severity="secondary" variant="text" @click="emit('cancelFilterDialog')" />
      <Button label="Clear All" severity="secondary" variant="outlined" @click="emit('clearDraftFilters')" />
      <Button label="Apply" @click="emit('applyFilters')" />
    </div>
  </template>
</Dialog>
```

### Footer Layout — Buttons Must Not Wrap

The footer uses two sibling divs. The left div MUST use `flex-1 min-w-0` (NOT `w-full`). The right div MUST use `shrink-0`.

| Element | Classes | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Left info div | `flex items-center flex-1 min-w-0` | Takes remaining space without forcing buttons to wrap |
| Right buttons div | `flex gap-sm shrink-0` | Never shrinks — prevents wrapping |

```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG — w-full pushes buttons to second line -->
<div class="flex items-center w-full">...</div>
<div class="flex gap-sm">...</div>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT — flex-1 + shrink-0 keeps single row -->
<div class="flex items-center flex-1 min-w-0">...</div>
<div class="flex gap-sm shrink-0">...</div>
```

## 3. DataTableToolbar — Correct Event Names and Props

The filter button and chips live in `DataTableToolbar`. Use these exact event names and props:

```html
<DataTableToolbar
  :showFilterButton="true"
  :showSaveViewButton="false"
  :activeFilters="activeFilterChips"
  :maxVisibleFilters="5"
  @filter="emit('openFilterDialog')"
  @clear-all="emit('clearAllFilters')"
  @filter-remove="emit('removeFilterChip', $event)"
/>
```

| Event | Toolbar emits | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| Filter button clicked | `filter` | Open the filter dialog |
| "Clear filter" link clicked | `clear-all` | Clear all applied filters |
| Chip X clicked | `filter-remove` | Remove one filter group |

> **⛔ The toolbar emits `clear-all` and `filter-remove` — NOT `clear-filters` or `remove-filter`. Using wrong event names silently fails.**

Always set `:showSaveViewButton="false"` unless saved views are explicitly needed.

## 4. Filter Chips — Grouped by Filter Type

Chips are **grouped per filter** — one chip per filter type, NOT one chip per value. Multi-value filters show a comma-separated summary.

### Formatting Rule

| Count | Display |
|---|---|
| 1 value | `Server \| is \| Github` |
| 2 values | `Server \| is \| Github, Figma` |
| 3+ values | `Server \| is \| Github, Figma, +1` |

### Helper Function

```ts
function formatGroupedValues(values: string[], maxVisible = 2): string {
  if (values.length <= maxVisible) return values.join(', ');
  return `${values.slice(0, maxVisible).join(', ')}, +${values.length - maxVisible}`;
}
```

### Chip Generation

Each filter produces **at most one chip**. The chip `id` is the filter key (e.g. `'user'`, `'status'`).

```ts
const activeFilterChips = computed(() => {
  const chips = [];
  if (appliedUsers.value.length > 0) {
    chips.push({ id: 'user', key: 'User', operator: 'is', value: formatGroupedValues(appliedUsers.value) });
  }
  if (appliedStatus.value !== 'All') {
    chips.push({ id: 'status', key: 'Status', operator: 'is', value: appliedStatus.value });
  }
  return chips;
});
```

### Chip Removal — Clears the Entire Group

Since each chip represents a filter group, removing a chip clears **all values** for that filter:

```ts
function removeFilterChip(chip: { id?: string }) {
  const chipId = chip.id ?? '';
  if (chipId === 'user') appliedUsers.value = [];
  else if (chipId === 'status') appliedStatus.value = 'All';
}
```

## 5. Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Correct Approach |
|---|---|
| Using `FilterModal` from Circuit DS | Use `Dialog` + `FormField` components |
| Placing filter inputs inline in the toolbar | Put them inside a `Dialog` opened by the filter button |
| Listening for `@clear-filters` on toolbar | Use `@clear-all` — that is the actual event name |
| Listening for `@remove-filter` on toolbar | Use `@filter-remove` — that is the actual event name |
| Using `w-full` on left footer div | Use `flex-1 min-w-0` to prevent button wrapping |
| One chip per selected value | One chip per filter group with `formatGroupedValues` |
| Removing chip removes single value | Removing chip clears the entire filter group |
| Forgetting `:showSaveViewButton="false"` | Always set it unless saved views are needed |
| Directly mutating applied state in dialog | Use draft refs; only copy to applied on "Apply" |
